COVID-19 Status

As of 3:21PM PT yesterday, over 1.4 million Canadians have tested positive for COVID-19. Sadly, 25.4 thousand have died.

In the last day, 3 thousand new infections were reported and 48 deaths. This is trending downwards.

Fortunately, 22.3 million doses of the vaccine have been administered. For those 12 years and older, 61.8% have their 1st shot and 5.4% are fully vaccinated!

Vaccination is speeding up, but there are 3.6 million doses in the freezer. It currently takes ~9 days for new deliveries to get into arms. At the current rate, all Canadians aged 12+ should have the first dose by Jul-09 and fully vaccinated by Oct-01. There is no approved vaccine for children aged 11 or younger.
